tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The results show a slightly elevated HbA1c at the upper limit of normal, suggesting possible impaired glucose regulation, and mild fasting hypoglycemia. Renal function, electrolytes, and calcium are within normal limits. Mildly decreased total CO₂ may indicate a tendency toward mild metabolic acidosis. Clinical correlation is recommended, especially regarding glucose metabolism and acid-base status.
